This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with routing protocols. It also involves the application of machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of deep reinforcement learning techniques could place it in the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper's focus on data-driven routing protocols could also place it in the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's potential implications for security could place it in the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
